        <div class="content">
          <p>The case study was developed by KTH-DESA to illustrate the basic features of energy systems modelling by using OSeMOSYS, the open source energy modelling system, and its interface MoManI. This exercise uses data for a fictitious country, called Atlantis, that shares features of both a developing and a developed countries. The interactive visualization presents results from four scenarios: a reference business-as-usual one where the country achieves universal access to electricity by 2030; another setting a 50 per cent target of electricity generation from renewables; and a climate change scenario.</p>

